N><VOLUNTARY_EX_ANTE_TRANSPARENCY_NOTICE CATEGORY="ORIGINAL" FORM="15" LG="EN" VERSION="R2.0.8.S03.E01"><FD_VOLUNTARY_EX_ANTE_TRANSPARENCY_NOTICE CTYPE="WORKS"><NOTICE_PUBLISHED NOTICE="CONTRACTING_AUTHORITY"/><CONTRACTING_AUTHORITY_VEAT><NAME_ADDRESSES_CONTACT_VEAT><CA_CE_CONCESSIONAIRE_PROFILE><ORGANISATION><OFFICIALNAME>Northern Ireland Housing Executive</OFFICIALNAME></ORGANISATION><ADDRESS>Corporate Procurement Unit, 6th Floor, The Housing Centre, 2 Adelaide Street</ADDRESS><TOWN>Belfast</TOWN><POSTAL_CODE>BT2 8PB</POSTAL_CODE><COUNTRY VALUE="UK"/><CONTACT_POINT>Ronan Matthews</CONTACT_POINT><ATTENTION>As above</ATTENTION><PHONE>+44 2895982665</PHONE><E_MAILS><E_MAIL>ronan.matthews@nihe.gov.uk</E_MAIL></E_MAILS></CA_CE_CONCESSIONAIRE_PROFILE><INTERNET_ADDRESSES_VEAT><URL_GENERAL>http://www.nihe.gov.uk</URL_GENERAL></INTERNET_ADDRESSES_VEAT></NAME_ADDRESSES_CONTACT_VEAT><TYPE_AND_ACTIVITIES_OR_CONTRACTING_ENTITY_AND_PURCHASING_ON_BEHALF><TYPE_AND_ACTIVITIES><TYPE_OF_CONTRACTING_AUTHORITY VALUE="REGIONAL_AUTHORITY"/><TYPE_OF_ACTIVITY VALUE="HOUSING_AND_COMMUNITY_AMENITIES"/></TYPE_AND_ACTIVITIES><PURCHASING_ON_BEHALF><PURCHASING_ON_BEHALF_NO/></PURCHASING_ON_BEHALF></TYPE_AND_ACTIVITIES_OR_CONTRACTING_ENTITY_AND_PURCHASING_ON_BEHALF></CONTRACTING_AUTHORITY_VEAT><OBJECT_VEAT><DESCRIPTION_VEAT><TITLE_CONTRACT><P>Intention to novate contracts following an insolvency event (specific contract details listed at II 1.4)</P></TITLE_CONTRACT><TYPE_CONTRACT_LOCATION><TYPE_CONTRACT VALUE="WORKS"/></TYPE_CONTRACT_LOCATION><LOCATION_NUTS><n2016:NUTS CODE="UKN"/></LOCATION_NUTS><SHORT_CONTRACT_DESCRIPTION><P>The purpose of this notice is to advise of the intention to novate contracts from Carillion Energy Services Limited and Carillion AMBS currently held by NIHE to Engie Regeneration Limited following an insolvency event. Contracts are due to novate no sooner than 10 days after the publication of this notice. There are 8 contracts effected by the novation process. The contracts were subject to OJEU competition in the past and awarded to Carillion Energy Services and Carillion AMBS. Following Carillion PLC entering insolvency on 15.1.2018, NIHE has been liaising with PwC and special managers regarding the continuation of services.</P><P>Heating Contract 2012 Belfast.</P><P>Heating Contract 2012 South East.</P><P>Maintenance and Improvement Lot 2 Belfast Region 2.</P><P>Maintenance and Improvement Lot 5 North Region 1.</P><P>Heating Services 2017 Lot 2 Belfast Region 2.</P><P>Heating Services 2017 Lot 5 North Region 1.</P><P>Mechanical and Electrical Services — Lot 2 Belfast Region.</P><P>Legionella Inspection Services.</P><P>NIHE considers that it is entitled to award the above listed contracts to ENGIE Regeneration Limited in accordance with Regulation 72 (1) (d) of the Public Contracts Regulations 2015 which specifically provides for a safe harbour allowing Contracting Authorities to modify existing contracts without a new procurement procedure.</P></SHORT_CONTRACT_DESCRIPTION><CPV><CPV_MAIN><CPV_CODE CODE="45210000"/></CPV_MAIN><CPV_ADDITIONAL><CPV_CODE CODE="50700000"/></CPV_ADDITIONAL><CPV_ADDITIONAL><CPV_CODE CODE="71314310"/></CPV_ADDITIONAL></CPV><CONTRACT_COVERED_GPA VALUE="NO"/></DESCRIPTION_VEAT><TOTAL_FINAL_VALUE><COSTS_RANGE_AND_CURRENCY_WITH_VAT_RATE CURRENCY="GBP"><VALUE_COST FMTVAL="204500000.00">204 500 000,00</VALUE_COST><EXCLUDING_VAT/></COSTS_RANGE_AND_CURRENCY_WITH_VAT_RATE></TOTAL_FINAL_VALUE></OBJECT_VEAT><PROCEDURE_DEFINITION_VEAT><TYPE_OF_PROCEDURE_DEF_F15><F15_AWARD_WITHOUT_PRIOR_PUBLICATION><ANNEX_D_F15><ANNEX_D1><NO_OPEN_RESTRICTED VALUE="OPEN_PROCEDURE"/><NO_MANUFACTURED_BY_DIRECTIVE/><NO_ONLY_IRREGULAR_INACCEPTABLE_TENDERERS/><REASON_CONTRACT_LAWFUL><P>Contracts currently in place with Carillion PLC subsidiaries were effected by the insolvency event on 15.1.2018. PwC were appointed as special managers and have been conducting business since that date. PwC are working with all parties to finalise an acquisition of the contracts held by Carillion for the provision of services to NIHE. The intention is to novate all contracts to Engie Regeneration Ltd at a time after the 10-day expiry of this notice following publication. In considering the novation, Public Contracts Regulations 2015, Reg 72 1 (d) is applied to enable the proposed novation of contracts. All terms and conditions will remain unchanged. The scope or value of contracts will not be effected.</P></REASON_CONTRACT_LAWFUL></ANNEX_D1></ANNEX_D_F15></F15_AWARD_WITHOUT_PRIOR_PUBLICATION></TYPE_OF_PROCEDURE_DEF_F15><AWARD_CRITERIA_VEAT_INFORMATION><AWARD_CRITERIA_DETAIL_F15><MOST_ECONOMICALLY_ADVANTAGEOUS_TENDER_SHORT><CRITERIA_DEFINITION><ORDER_C>1</ORDER_C><CRITERIA>The criteria published in the original tender documentation (OJEU ref XXXX)</CRITERIA><WEIGHTING>100</WEIGHTING></CRITERIA_DEFINITION></MOST_ECONOMICALLY_ADVANTAGEOUS_TENDER_SHORT></AWARD_CRITERIA_DETAIL_F15><F15_IS_ELECTRONIC_AUCTION_USABLE VALUE="NO"/></AWARD_CRITERIA_VEAT_INFORMATION><ADMINISTRATIVE_INFORMATION_VEAT><PREVIOUS_PUBLICATION_INFORMATION_NOTICE_F15><PREVIOUS_PUBLICATION_EXISTS_F15><CNT_NOTICE_INFORMATION><CNT_NOTICE_INFORMATION_S CHOICE="CONTRACT_NOTICE"/><NOTICE_NUMBER_OJ>2016/S 017-025995</NOTICE_NUMBER_OJ><DATE_OJ><DAY>26</DAY><MONTH>01</MONTH><YEAR>2016</YEAR></DATE_OJ></CNT_NOTICE_INFORMATION><NO_OTHER_PREVIOUS_PUBLICATION/></PREVIOUS_PUBLICATION_EXISTS_F15></PREVIOUS_PUBLICATION_INFORMATION_NOTICE_F15></ADMINISTRATIVE_INFORMATION_VEAT></PROCEDURE_DEFINITION_VEAT><AWARD_OF_CONTRACT_DEFENCE><ECONOMIC_OPERATOR_NAME_ADDRESS><CONTACT_DATA_WITHOUT_RESPONSIBLE_NAME><ORGANISATION><OFFICIALNAME>Engie Regeneration Limited</OFFICIALNAME></ORGANISATION><ADDRESS>Q3 Office Quorum Business Park Benton Lane Newcastle Upon Tyne NE12 8EX</ADDRESS><TOWN>Newcastle upon Tyne</TOWN><COUNTRY VALUE="UK"/></CONTACT_DATA_WITHOUT_RESPONSIBLE_NAME></ECONOMIC_OPERATOR_NAME_ADDRESS><MORE_INFORMATION_TO_SUB_CONTRACTED><NO_CONTRACT_LIKELY_SUB_CONTRACTED/></MORE_IN